latestPosts.caption:
Today, I get to talk about my sister, Janvi Turakhia—a kind of person you don’t really find in this generation. Someone who speaks with all her heart, thinks with all her mind, and fights with all her soul.

She’s a mother of two—me first, then her real baby (who’s also mine).

She’s the kind of person who will give you her last bite of food without a second thought. Who will stay up after a long night just to make sure you’re home safe, not drunk or crying alone. The kind of mother who has put everything on hold to give her baby the best life possible. The kind of daughter who would do anything to keep a frown from our mom’s face.

If you ask me who the better daughter is—it’s her, hands down. The most selfless human to ever exist.

Is she scary? Absolutely. Because the things we write in notes, she’ll say straight to your face (loudly) until you finally listen.
Is she funny? Unfortunately, yes. Because her laugh is terrible, and she finds everything hilarious—but somehow, it’s contagious, and you’ll always end up smiling.

My sister is my world, and no one can possibly love her more than I do.

When you’re sad, she makes sure the whole night revolves around you—everyone else is just background noise. When you’re sick, she’s the first to show up and the last to leave. If it’s your birthday, there’s no chance you won’t receive exactly what you wanted—because she’s impossible to beat at that game. And if you’ve had a fight with someone, trust that she’ll always pick the right side.

She’s almost magical. She’s my sister. And today, she’s officially a granny.

Happy birthday, Didi.
35 years of making mom the proudest showrunner.
28 years of keeping me as safe as safe gets.
And 2 years of being the absolute best mother in the universe to our angel.

I love you! @janviturakiamalik
